The paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new method for this task, which involves disentangling the content and attribute representations of images and fitting the attribute space with a Gaussian mixture model (GMM). This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multi-domain and multi-modal image-to-image translation, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
